			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    <B>* Everlore's Guide to Pottery</B></b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:BrandonP@obsidian-tech.com">Dieciden (Brandon Parker)</a> | 
		            9/13/2000 1:06:33 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2"><table border="0" cellspacing="1" width="100%">
    <tr>
      <td>

<p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b><a name="Pottery:">Pottery:</a></b></font></p>
<ul>
  <li><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a href="#Introduction:">Introduction</a></font></li>
  <li><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a href="#What you need to make your first pot:">What
    you need to make your first pot</a></font></li>
  <li><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a href="#Where you can find these items:">Where
    you can find pottery components</a></font></li>
  <li><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a href="#How to make your first pot:">How
    to make you first pot</a></font></li>
  <li><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a href="#The Pottery Recipe Book:">The
    Pottery recipe Book</a></font></li>
</ul>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><b><a name="Introduction:">Introduction:</a></b></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Pottery
in my opinion a very valuable and under used trade skill. It has a great potential
for profit gain because other trade skill require what you can make while
potting. However pottery can be very expensive when beginning, because it is
very component intensive (that is to say that there are many thing to buy). And
pottery is one of the only multiple step skills, so you will fail quite often in
the beginning. When you decide to undertake the rigors of the professional
potting scene, the very first thing you must do is invest at least 10 practice
points into your potting skill. This is <a href="http://www.everlore.com">Everlore</a>'s
policy in almost all trade skills as it will save you money, time, and trade
skill components.</font></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"> </p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font face="Verdana" size="2"><b><a name="What you need to make your first pot:">What
you need to make your first pot:</a></b></font></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"> </p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font face="Verdana" size="2">There
are quite a lot of items you will need to purchase
in order to make your first pot. Here is a list: </font></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"> </p>
<div align="center">
  <table border="3" cellspacing="1" width="51%" height="177" bordercolorlight="#C0C0C0" bordercolordark="#666666">
    <tr>
      <td width="27%" height="27"><b><font face="Verdana" size="2">Item</font></b></td>
      <td width="72%" height="27"><b><font face="Verdana" size="2">Description </font></b></td>
      <td width="9%" height="27"><b><font face="Verdana" size="2">Picture</font></b></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width="27%" height="28"><font face="Verdana" size="2">"Guide to Pottery"</font></td>
      <td width="72%" height="28"><font face="Verdana" size="2">A book</font></td>
      <td width="9%" height="28"><img border="0" src="http://www.everlore.com/files2/Book.jpg" width="49" height="49"></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width="27%" height="28"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Clay</font></td>
      <td width="72%" height="28"><font face="Verdana" size="2">What the pot is made out of.</font></td>
      <td width="9%" height="28"><img border="0" src="http://www.everlore.com/files2/Clay.jpg" width="49" height="49"></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width="27%" height="30"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Sketches</font></td>
